@@ -0,0 +1,112 @@
+# Work Assistant
+
+The work assistant is an integrated Hermis Life OS module, not a separate app. It runs inside the existing Discord tracker sidecar, writes to the same tracker database, and mirrors useful state into the Life OS filesystem.
+
+## Goals
+
+- Track to-do items quickly from Discord.
+- Organize work by priority, due date, project, context, and blocked/waiting state.
+- Produce a short focus plan instead of a long task dump.
+- Retrieve local Life OS context when needed without searching raw/private logs by default.
+- Create a continuous improvement loop for repeated work friction.
+
+## Files
+
+- Bot integration: `apps/discord_tracker/bot.py`
+- Work parser: `apps/discord_tracker/work.py`
+- Work storage: `apps/discord_tracker/work_store.py`
+- Runtime database: `data/lifeos_tracker.db`
+- Work logs: `data/work/YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl` and `data/work/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
+- Current work snapshot: `state/work.md`
+- Work reviews: `reports/work/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
+- Daily review script: `scripts/summarize_work_day.py`
+
+## Setup
+
+Add these optional values to `.env.discord-tracker`:
+
+```dotenv
+WORK_CHANNEL_NAME=work-tracker
+WORK_MORNING_PLAN_HOUR=14
+WORK_SHUTDOWN_REVIEW_HOUR=23
+```
+
+Create a Discord channel named `#work-tracker`, or change `WORK_CHANNEL_NAME`.
+
+The bot needs the same Discord permissions already required by the tracker sidecar:
+
+- View Channels
+- Send Messages
+- Read Message History
+- Use Message Content Intent
+
+## Capture format
+
+Any non-command owner message in `#work-tracker` is captured as work. Multiline messages become multiple work items.
+
+Examples:
+
+```text
+todo: send client update priority:p1 due:2026-05-04 project:Acme @email #client 20m
+urgent fix deployment issue today project:Hermes @code
+blocked: waiting for invoice details project:Admin
+someday make a reusable onboarding checklist project:LifeOS
+```
+
+Parsed fields:
+
+- Priority: `p0`, `p1`, `p2`, `p3`, or words like `urgent`, `important`, `backlog`.
+- Due date: `due:YYYY-MM-DD`, `today`, `tomorrow`, weekday names, or `in N days`.
+- Project: `[Project]` prefix or `project:Name`.
+- Context: `@email`, `@code`, `@call`, etc.
+- Tags: `#client`, `#admin`, etc.
+- Effort: `20m`, `1h`, or `effort:45`.
+- Energy: `energy:low`, `energy:medium`, `energy:high`.
+
+## Commands
+
+- `!work` or `!work list` — show active work.
+- `!work add <task>` — add one task; multiline text creates multiple tasks.
+- `!work today` — show the focus plan for today.
+- `!work focus` — same as today; optimized for what to do next.
+- `!work done <id>` — mark an item done.
+- `!work block <id> <reason>` — mark an item blocked.
+- `!work wait <id> <reason>` — mark an item waiting.
+- `!work cancel <id> <reason>` — cancel an item.
+- `!work info <query>` — search compiled Life OS context in `wiki/`, `state/`, `reports/`, `memory/curated/`, `data/daily-summary/`, and `data/work/`.
+- `!work improve <idea>` — add an improvement candidate.
+- `!work review` — write `reports/work/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.
+
+## Automation
+
+The bot posts two daily prompts in `#work-tracker`, aligned with the user's Casablanca work window (14:00-23:00 by default):
+
+1. Workday start focus plan at `WORK_MORNING_PLAN_HOUR`.
+2. Workday shutdown review prompt at `WORK_SHUTDOWN_REVIEW_HOUR`.
+
+The prompts are idempotent because they use the existing `posted_reminders` table with `kind='work'`.
+
+For a deterministic end-of-day report, run:
+
+```bash
+scripts/summarize_work_day.py <YYYY-MM-DD>
+```
+
+## Memory and retrieval policy
+
+Work can contain sensitive company/client context. By default:
+
+- Raw work captures remain local in `raw/captures/`.
+- Detailed work events remain local in `data/work/` and SQLite.
+- Hermes/OpenViking should index `wiki/`, `state/work.md`, and user-approved curated work memories first.
+- The `!work info` command searches compiled/local Life OS text and intentionally skips raw captures, raw documents, tracker DB rows, env files, and backups.
+
+## Continuous improvement loop
+
+At the end of a workday, add friction or automation ideas with:
+
+```text
+!work improve Make invoice sending a checklist/template
+```
+
+Weekly review should inspect open improvement candidates and decide whether to automate, template, delegate, clarify, or delete each one.
